message.content:
A white refrigerator stands against the wall to the right of tall black cabinetry; the cabinetry extends along an L-shaped kitchen corner topped by a beige marble-like counter. On this counter near the refrigerator sit a jar labeled “Bonne Maman Strawberry Preserves,” a box of strawberry-flavored Jell-O, and a container labeled “Alpen Salz.” Further along the same counter, a short stack of white plates is next to two cereal boxes—one labeled “Rice Bubbles” and another labeled “Chucky”—alongside an additional jam jar and an orange mug. A small metal pot is on a stovetop set into the counter’s corner, with a wooden vent hood above it. A stainless-steel sink is located beneath a wooden-framed window on the adjacent counter segment.

Opposite the kitchen area is a rectangular wooden dining table surrounded by white-upholstered chairs. At the center of the table, a large plastic water bottle labeled “Evian” rests in a white caddy, next to a square box labeled “Shortbread” and a white fruit bowl containing several oranges and a lemon. A clear pitcher and a single wine glass sit nearby. A white door is positioned behind the table, and the room floor is laid with brown parquet, while the walls are painted white.
